releases.name: v1.0.0
releases.body: Safety Delta-Delta v1.0.0 is the initial release of the library.  It's purpose is to visualize change over time between two measures.  For more information check the project out on [GitHub Pages](https://rhoinc.github.io/safety-delta-delta/) and try it out [here](https://rhoinc.github.io/safety-delta-delta/test-page/example1/).

issues.title: Fix Visit Documentation
issues.body: Copy/paste error in `visit` documentation found in setting schema and wiki.

issues.title: 0.00 Change Over Time values are showing as -0.00 in the details table and are red
issues.body: All of the 0.00 Change Over Time values that I can find in the details table for a participant are showing as "-0.00" and are red, instead of showing as 0.00 and being colored black.

issues.title: Non-existent value for a required field gives mixed results
issues.body:
For Medical Sign or Result, if I enter a non-existent value for these fields, the chart will not render and shows an error message: "There might've been some problems initializing the chart. Errors include:
TypeError: d[_this.config.measure_col] is undefined". There is a spinning wheel below the error message.

For Result, ID, Visit, Visit (Numeric), and Measures; if I enter an invalid value, the chart renders, but shows no data points. It also does not show any kind of error message. At no point do I see a "variable does not exist error", either in the developer tools Console output, or in the container element.

issues.title: Units not appearing for measures
issues.body:
Per the test note below, units should be attached to the measures when you set initial X or Y measures, but I don't see units in the measures fields, whether I set an initial starting measure or not. 

"Confirm that if you set initial X or Y Measure to an existent value (like IgE) and render, then the chart defaults to the specified measure, but with units attached. [[[TODO: ADD CODE]]]"

issues.title: Number of missing and non-numeric records not appearing in chart
issues.body: Per the test notes, missing or non-numeric values in the dataset should be handled and removed, and the "number of missing and non-numeric records appears opposite the number of participants annotation, beneath the controls". I believe that missing values are being handled, as I can see in the developer tools console that they have been removed, but I do not see any text in the chart to indicate to a user that values have been removed.

issues.title: Fix precision of data points between chart points and detail table
issues.body: When you click on a data point in the chart, the details table shows the change over time values to two decimal precision. When you hover over a data point in the chart, it shows the values to three decimal precision. This can lead to values that don't quite seem to match, i.e., 0.005 when hovering shows as 0.00 in the details table. Seems like the precision should be the same in both places so that the values match.
